From:Paul Senior
IPG is poorly managed and overly diversified (e.g. their "ill-fated" entry into
the auto racing business being the most egregious). Those issues are what's
hurt the company.

IPG is a substantial company - 43,000 employees. I don't see revenue growth,
but still, there's $15 now in revenue behind every share. Given that the ad
business is cyclical, and this year brings the Olympics and Nov. election, next
year may be worse for IPG (business and stock) than this year.

My bet is that the stock might be expected to drop again to a point or two
under $10, but since the problems with IPG seem to be all publicly known now,
and there's a turnaround plan presumably in place and being executed, I can bet
small that the stock might recover again to $15 or better within 12-18 months -
if the market doesn't crash.
