From:Jurgis Bekepuris
Late reply:

"I am just concerned when a stock drops as much as this and one is adding for a
third time."

I have no opinion on SHRP, but I have a comment on your comment. :) I have
added to stocks that dropped more percentage-wise than SHRP. Actually, now I
usually (note: "usually" :))) add every time stock drops to 0.75-0.8 of my last
purchase price. Of course, I have to be sure that there are no issues with the
company and its future to do that. If I discover such issues, I sell
immediately even at a loss.

Note that I only invest in companies with high ROE possibly temporarily (!?!?)
fallen on tough times. I don't usually buy high D/E companies losing money, so
except for fraud or total company collapse, I am somewhat protected from the
worst outcome.

How has this worked? Fine for me, although I have sold some companies at a loss
for issues that did not come to roost. I also got some good positions in stocks
that were hated for no reason. ARMHY is probably the biggest success story.

You pay your money and you make your choices. :)

Jurgis
